# <type>: <short summary> (50 chars max)
#
# Types: feat | fix | refactor | chore | docs | style | test
#
# WHY this change was needed (not what — the diff shows that):
#
#
# ─────────────────────────────────
# Examples of GOOD commit messages:
#   fix: bootstrap SQLite tables inline — prisma db push not available in standalone
#   feat: add SafetyMeter component — shows quota usage before LinkedIn bans you
#   refactor: move auth to JWT cookies — Flask sessions don't work in Next.js
#
# Examples of BAD commit messages:
#   "update"
#   "fix stuff"
#   "feat: initial Next.js 16 migration — full TypeScript rewrite"  ← too big, no WHY
